    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-09T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="1338"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1338">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.56374/7–954: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1338<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom (<persName
                            corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from">Aldrich</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1338fn1">Repeated priority to Cairo as telegram 3.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-09T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 9, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. Limit distribution. Foreign Office informed Embassy today in strict
                    confidence that Stevenson putting new British proposals on Suez base to
                    Egyptians tomorrow.<note n="2" xml:id="d1338fn2">Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_AWW1">Aldrich</persName> reported in telegram 12, July 1,
                        not printed, that the Foreign Office was sending instructions to Stevenson
                        to be prepared to approach the Egyptians after <persName corresp="#p_ESA1"
                            >Eden</persName>’s return, which was expected on July 6.
                        (641.74/7–154)</note> No announcement will be made and British hope for
                    absolute secrecy for next few days. <persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        >Churchill</persName> is meeting with group of Conservatives July 13 to
                    explain proposals. It expected <persName corresp="#p_BV1">Butler</persName> and
                    Head (Minister of War. will participate in this discussion but not <persName
                        corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName>, in order stress proposals have full
                    Cabinet support rather than being merely Foreign Office inspired. Next day some
                    sort of announcement will probably be made in House Commons.</p>
                <p>In effort improve atmosphere for resumption of talks British decided release
                    pounds 10 million Egyptian sterling balances and Stevenson has so informed
                    Egyptians. According to report just received <pb facs="0577" n="2279"
                        xml:id="pg_2279"/> from him this has had extremely favorable reaction.
                    Foreign Office tells us some consideration was given to making release
                    conditional on relaxation Egyptian trade restrictions but it finally decided not
                    make this absolute condition, although Stevenson was instructed to ask for, and
                    received, oral assurances on this score.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Aldrich</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
